headline: Austria’s Kurz to Govern With Green Party in Unlikely Pairing
abstract: After months of talks, Sebastian Kurz’s conservatives and progressive Greens agreed on a coalition that could be a harbinger for the rest of Europe.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Seven months after his coalition with the far right collapsed in a spectacular scandal, Sebastian Kurz, Austria’s former conservative chancellor, stood before television cameras on Thursday and announced a new government — this time with the progressive Greens.
